about.summary: Another command line download utility written in python

name: wgetter
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "wgetter" %}
{% set version = "0.7" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b6a4bef1a095e354d1dd24232947f5ee6cd5c6a63e0e34aeb9d7575620c371ee

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - wgetter
 
about:
  home: https://github.com/phoemur/wgetter
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  # PR to get license_file into src distribution: https://github.com/phoemur/wgetter/pull/4
  license_file: '{{ environ["RECIPE_DIR"] }}/LICENSE'
  summary: Another command line download utility written in python

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - npavlovikj
